@mahmoud Hmm, file objects can be open in either bytes or unicode mode in Python 3. Sniff the mode attribute and look for a 'b' to verify it's bytes mode, otherwise it's reading unicodes.

It should be fine to not have to wrap the files at all - just verify they'll return the right kind of data and then leave them in the right place in the sequence (assuming they support seek).

Also agree that handling the Spooled{Bytes,String}IO instances seems reasonable. I didn't think of that because I didn't have such a requirement in hg. :)

