Your solution is simple and elegant. Here is my ideas:

To my opinion, json support empty string as key, so you can create key-related validations like:
```json
{ "": "enum:param1|param2:any" }
{ "": "str:any" }
{ "": "datetime:%Y%m%d:any" }
```

or you can split key-validations and value-validations like:
```json
{ "": { "key": "str:param1|str:param2", "value": "any" } }
{ "": { "key": "str:any", "value": "any" } }
{ "": { "key": "datetime:%Y%m%d", "value": "any" } }
```

maybe you can support multi key-value validations like:
```json
{
  "": {
    "str:param1|str:param2": "any",
    "regex:[0-9]{3,5}": "any",
    "datetime:%Y%m%d": "int"
  }
}
```

That's all, :)

