Faceted navigation is using only the **content-core** metal-slot from your template, everything else is ignored. Thus, you can put your CSS within portal_css with a specific condition. Same for JS within portal_javascripts with mention that you can bind Faceted specific events to trigger your code:

```
jQuery(document).ready( function() {
  if(window.Faceted){
    jQuery(Faceted.Events).bind(Faceted.Events.AJAX_QUERY_SUCCESS, function(){
      shopFunction();
    });
  }
});
```

Here is the list of all Faceted specific events: https://github.com/eea/eea.facetednavigation/blob/master/eea/facetednavigation/browser/javascript/view.js#L4

