You'll have to check the documentation site in the current README to see how the configuration options have changed.  There's a migration guide there to help you get away from the legacy ``datatable_options`` syntax and begin using ``DataTable`` classes, which are like django's ModelForm and represent columns.  In the simplest cases, you can still just whitelist columns for inclusion and shouldn't be too troublesome.

Basically the new syntax would look like this in your case:

```python
class CarDatatable(Datatable):
    class Meta:
        columns = ['reference', 'name']

class CareDatatableView(DatatableView):
    datatable_class = CarDatatable

```

