Another solution is to attach the runtime data to the instance, example:

```python
class Entity(Model):
    parameter = StringType()

    @serializable(type=URLType)
    def entity_url(self)
        if self.parameter is not None and hasattr(self, 'app_data'):
            request = self.app_data.get('request')
            entity_route = request.app.route['entities']  # aiohttp-like router, for example
            return entity_route.url_for(parameter=self.parameter)

def handler(request):
    my_entity = Entity()
    my_entity.app_data = {'request': request}
    print my_entity.serialize()

```

